column7: xBRL_ Document Information. Entries Type. Code
column8: account: information to fill in a chart of accounts file. balance: the results of accumulation of a complete and validated list of entries for an account or a list of account in a specific period - sometimes called general ledger entries: a list of individual accounting entries, which might be posted/validated or nonposted/n journal: a self-balancing Dr= Cr list of entries for a specific period including beginning balance for that period. ledger: a complete list of entries for a specific account or list of accounts for a specific period; note - debits do not have to equal credits. assets: a listing of open receivables, payables, inventory, fixed assets or other information that can be extracted from but are not necessarily included as part of a journal n trialBalance: the self-balancing Dr= Cr result of accumulation of a complete and validated list of entries for the entity in a complete list of accounts in a specific period. taxtables: aids automated interpretation of instances that represent tax tables; Tax table are defined by using multiple [taxes] structures to gather the population of codes, authorities and rates; through [taxTableCode] cross-references in the [taxes] structure, these 'master file' tax tables can be referenced. mapping: a collection of mappings between interrelated data sets, such as a local and related corporate standard chart of accounts or detail data mapped to summarized end reporting concepts. versioning: a collection of changes between two versions of the same class of information, such as updates to a master file like a chart of accounts. master_file: a collection of master files, such as the customer or inventory master file. trade_documents: a collection of trade/transactional documents, such as vendor invoices or customer orders. profile_compliant: the meaning of this collection of information can be determined by understanding an established profile and especially an XBRL GL Profile. Profiles are determined through namespace declarations, schemaRef and conventions of those profiles. other: for all other types of representations. Often sorted by date or by account, these terms have specific, and sometimes different, meanings in different areas. Common practice will drive accounting method/term matches.

column7: xBRL_ Entry Detail. Posting Date. Date Time
column8: At the detail level, this represents the accounting significance date. No matter what date the document is received, entered, or posted, this signifies the accounting date of the entry. If you want to see the financial results for March 5, 2002 and this entry is given that date, the entry will be part of the results for March 5, 2002. This is different from the postedDate found at the entryHeader level. If you want the accounting significance to be a particular date, it goes here. A single entry could represent multiple dates, but would only be posted on one date.

column7: xBRL_ Entry Detail. Specified. xBRL_ Monetary Amount
column8: This field amount represents the primary monetary amount related to the subject of the entryDetail line. There is one primary monetary amount per entryDetail structure. It may, for example, represent the amount of one line of a journal entry, the balance on a document, or the extended amount of a line item on an invoice. Amount is not required if detailed entry is used for non-financial work and other elements are populated, in particular measurableQuantity. The amount field is a signed number either positive or negative itself and used in conjunction with a separate signOfAmount and a separate debitCreditCode, which together are considered for understanding the monetary amount. The unit of measure is determined by amountCurrency if present, and by the default or home currency if amountCurrency is not present.

column8: If triangulation is used, amount in triangulation currency, for multi-currency tracking. Debit is entered as positive, credit as negative.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency. Amount Triangulation_ Currency. Code
column8: The currency used for triangulation, if used. May often be EUR or USD. Recommended ISO 4217 coding.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency. National Triangulation_ Exchange Rate. Numeric
column8: Exchange rate between national currency and triangulation currency at time of original transaction expressed as national currency divided by triangulation currency

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency. National Triangulation_ Source
column8: Source of Exchange Rate for triangulation amount at time of original transaction - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency. National Triangulation_ Type
column8: Type of Exchange Rate for triangulation amount at time of original transaction - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency. Original Triangulation_ Exchange Rate. Numeric
column8: Exchange rate between original currency and triangulation currency at time of original transaction expressed as original currency divided by triangulation currency

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency. Original Triangulation_ Source
column8: Source of Exchange Rate for triangulation from original currency to triangulation currency at time of original transaction - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency. Original Triangulation_ Type
column8: Type of Exchange Rate for triangulation from original currency to triangulation currency at time of original transaction - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency. Specified. xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail
column8: Section to provide additional information related to home currencies that differ from original currencies and related exchange rates - typically this will be used to record exchange rates and amounts in currencies and/or on dates other than those of the original transaction. This structure allows recording of exchange rates using a third currency as a triangulation currency. This is often EUR but is not restricted to being so. This structure may be repeated as many times as necessary to record amounts in foreign currencies on the same or different dates.

Section to provide additional information related to home currencies that differ from original currencies and related exchange rates - typically this will be used to record exchange rates and amounts in currencies and/or on dates other than those of the original transaction. This structure allows recording of exchange rates using a third currency as a triangulation currency. This is often EUR but is not restricted to being so. This structure may be repeated as many times as necessary to record amounts in foreign currencies on the same or different dates.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Exchange Rate Date. Date Time

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Amount Restated_ Amount
column8: The amount in the foreign currency identified by amountRestatedCurrency as of multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Amount Restated_ Currency. Code
column8: The currency in which amountRestatedAmount is expressed. Recommended ISO 4217 coding.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Amount Restated_ Exchange Rate. Numeric
column8: Exchange rate used to convert amountRestatedAmount as of multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate expressed as national currency divided by foreign currency

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Amount Restated_ Exchange Rate Source
column8: Source of Exchange Rate for restated amount - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Amount Restated_ Exchange Rate Type
column8: Type of Exchange Rate for restated amount - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Amount Triangulation_ Amount
column8: The amount in the triangulation currency identified by amountTriangulationCurrency as of multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Amount Triangulation_ Currency. Code
column8: The currency used for tringulation between amountRestatedCurrency and the home currency. Recommended ISO 4217 coding.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Amount Triangulation_ Exchange Rate. Numeric
column8: Exchange rate used to convert amountTriangulationAmount as of multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate expressed as national currency divided by triangulation currency

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Amount Triangulation_ Exchange Rate Source
column8: Source of Exchange Rate for triangulation amount - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Amount Triangulation_ Exchange Rate Type
column8: Type of Exchange Rate for triangulation amount - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Restated Triangulation_ Exchange Rate. Numeric
column8: Exchange rate used to convert from amountRestatedAmount to amountTriangulationAmount as of multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate expressed as foreign currency divided by triangulation currency

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Restated Triangulation_ Exchange Rate Source
column8: Source of Exchange Rate for converting between foreign currency and triangulation currency - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Restated Triangulation_ Exchange Rate Type
column8: Type of Exchange Rate for converting between foreign currency and triangulation currency - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

column7: xBRL_ Multi Currency Detail. Detail Comment
column8: Comment describing the enclosing multicurrencyDetail tuple's contents. May include reason for recording additional exchange rates other than that used at the time of the original transaction.

column7: xBRL_ Document. Apply To Number. Code
column8: Document number of primary invoice number, used to offset payments, debits and credits; for an invoice, usually the same as the documentNumber. Internal reference for the document above; number assigned internally to track the document
Date and less likely in the paper world but possible in the e-world, time on actual document invoice, voucher, check date. Other dates control posting information.

column7: xBRL_ Document. Received Date. Date Time
column8: Date/time document was noted as received if necessary. Represents actual date received. Posting dates are maintained separately.

Document location as URI, file name or other reference. Alternatively, text of document can be placed here.

Parent for information regarding measurable items associated with the enclosing entryDetail line. Primary area used for holding performance measures. Based on needs for tracking inventory transactional detail, but suitable for anything assigned to an 'account', 'reporting bucket' or 'code'. Can be used to track any movements.

Code for measurable item including BP - Business process, FA - Fixed asset/Capitalized item, IN - Inventory, KPI - Metric, NT - Intangible, SP - Supplies, SV-P - Service by employee, vendor or contractor, SV-M - Service by equipment/machinery, OT - Other
Free format description of the measurable code
Category of the measurable
Internal inventory part or SKU number or other code identifier for the measurable.
URI or other identifier for schema with which measurable ID can be validated
Second identifier such as vendor's item number
URI or other identifier for schema with which measurable ID Other can be validated
Text description of measurable e.g. inventory item or other identifier
Number of units in this transaction; for non-monetary calculations; can be square footage, number of people, etc.
Field that can represent grading, inspection codes, ratings and other qualifiers to properly capture PKI/Balanced Scorecard information
Description of unit: e.g. each, case, dozen, etc. ISO standard coding recommended.

column7: xBRL_ Measureable. Cost Per Unit. Amount

column7: xBRL_ Enhanced Measurable. Class ID. Code

column8: Free format description associated with gl-ehm:costingMethodCode to provide specialization of clarification for the enumerated value of other.

column7: xBRL_ Enhanced Measurable. Specified. xBRL_ Serial Lot
column8: Tuple for holding information about serial numbers or lots batches. As a tuple, this permits multiple serial numbers or multiple lot number batches within a single gl-cor:measurable structure.
Tuple for holding information about serial numbers or lots batches. As a tuple, this permits multiple serial numbers or multiple lot number batches within a single gl-cor:measurable structure.

Is this item tracked by serial numbers or lot numbers? A serial number is usually a unique number assigned to a single; a lot or batch number is provided when a batch of items is fungible but must be differentiated from similar items from other batches. Enumerated indicator for serial or lot items. Enumeration are: serial, lot, other, neither. If not included within the tuple, neither is assumed.

Free format description associated with gl-ehm:serialLotCode to provide specialization and especially to provide clarification for the enumerated value of other in serialLotCode. Examples might be "batch" or "group".
The holder for that actual serial number or lot batch number/code assigned to an item or a batch of items.

column7: xBRL_ Serial Lot. Next Serial Lot Number
column8: A field for holding the next expected serial or lot number to be given to future assignments, or for chaining between already assigned items.
The quantity of units in this particular batch. Unit of measure is the gl-bus:measurableUnitofMeasure.
The quantity of units in this batch on inception.
The remaining quantity of units from the original batch; may be the same as the quantity in this batch or include other batches from the same original batch.

column7: xBRL_ Serial Lot. Origination. Date Time

column7: xBRL_ Serial Lot. Expiration. Date Time
column8: Expiration date of the batch.
Manufacturer of the item serial or items lot/batch.
A name or description of the items in the lot or batch.

column7: xBRL_ Serial Lot. Warranty Start Date. Date Time
column8: If the items are covered by warranty, when that warranty covered will begin or has begun.

column7: xBRL_ Serial Lot. Warranty End Date. Date Time
column8: If the items are covered by warranty, when that warranty covered will end or ended.

column7: xBRL_ Serial Lot. Warranty Period. Numeric
column8: Warranty period - numeric portion; for a 30 day warranty period, the 30 would go here, and the day would go in gl-ehm:serialLotWarrantyPeriodUnit.

column7: xBRL_ Serial Lot. Warranty Period Unit
column8: Warrant period - time or cycle unit portion. Values from the XBRL Unit Registry (www.xbrl.org/utr/utr.xml) are suggested where possible. Examples might include: H (hours), D (days), M (months), Y (years), machine cycles, km (kilometers).
The vendor providing warranty; this may differ from the manufacturer.
Contract or document information related to the warranty, such as a contract number and date or a URL with more information.
Free format text related to the serial number or lot.
